i.d: The total return incorporates the price change for a period and any relevant dividends for the same period.
The 1 week total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends for the last week.
The 52 weeks total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends for the last 52 weeks.
The 1 month total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends for the last month.
The 3 months total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends for the last 3 months.
The 6 months total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends for the last 6 months.
The YTD total return incorporates the price change and any relevant dividends over the period of the year to date.

If there are no trades during the 10 day period, the value is zero. Each exchange has its own threshold for volume which may change over time depending upon trading activity. Non-block volume is defined as the volume when the trade is less than the threshold number of shares in a single trade.

i.d: The intersection of the 30 Day Simple Moving Average (SMA) with the 200 Day SMA. Determines whether the shorter term Simple Moving Average line has a positive, negative, or no intersection with the longer term Simple Moving Average line over a specified number of data points (days). A positive intersection is one where the short term line starts out below the long term line and ends up above it, and vice versa for a negative intersection. A positive intersect (P) indicates Buy opportunity and negative intersect (N) indicates Sell opportunity. X indicates no intersection between the two SMA lines. N/A N/D indicates insufficent data for us to calculate SMA's for the periods in question.
